      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the ciabatta is golden and crisp, remove the tray[s] from the oven and set aside to cool slightly, then rub the sliced-side of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>over it (not a fan of raw garlic? Only use a little!)</p><p>Top with the <strong>crumbled</strong> <strong>goats' cheese</strong>, drizzle over the<strong> remaining honey</strong>, your <strong>truffle oil </strong>(not a fan of truffle oil? Just add a little!) and the<strong> remaining dried thyme</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>– these are your<strong> goats' cheese montaditos</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
